verses.text: Woe to thee that spoilest , and thou \add wast\add* not spoiled ; and dealest treacherously , and they dealt not treacherously with thee! when thou shalt cease to spoil , thou shalt be spoiled ; \add and\add* when thou shalt make an end to deal treacherously , they shall deal treacherously with thee.
O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, be gracious unto us; we have waited for thee: be thou their arm every morning , our salvation also in the time of trouble.
At the noise of the tumult the people fled ; at the lifting up of thyself the nations were scattered.
And your spoil shall be gathered \add like\add* the gathering of the caterpiller : as the running to and fro of locusts shall he run upon them.
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* is exalted ; for he dwelleth on high : he hath filled Zion with judgment and righteousness.

And wisdom and knowledge shall be the stability of thy times , \add and\add* strength of salvation : the fear of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* his treasure.\f + \fr 33.6 \ft salvation: Heb. salvations\f*
Behold, their valiant ones shall cry without : the ambassadors of peace shall weep bitterly.\f + \fr 33.7 \ft valiant…: or, messengers\f*
The highways lie waste , the wayfaring man ceaseth : he hath broken the covenant , he hath despised the cities , he regardeth no man.

The earth mourneth \add and\add* languisheth : Lebanon is ashamed \add and\add* hewn down : Sharon is like a wilderness ; and Bashan and Carmel shake off \add their fruits\add*.\f + \fr 33.9 \ft hewn…: or, withered away\f*
Now will I rise , saith the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; now will I be exalted ; now will I lift up myself.
Ye shall conceive chaff , ye shall bring forth stubble : your breath , \add as\add* fire , shall devour you.
And the people shall be \add as\add* the burnings of lime : \add as\add* thorns cut up shall they be burned in the fire. \p
¶ Hear , ye \add that are\add* far off , what I have done ; and, ye \add that are\add* near , acknowledge my might.
The sinners in Zion are afraid ; fearfulness hath surprised the hypocrites. Who among us shall dwell with the devouring fire ? who among us shall dwell with everlasting burnings ?

He that walketh righteously , and speaketh uprightly ; he that despiseth the gain of oppressions , that shaketh his hands from holding of bribes , that stoppeth his ears from hearing of blood , and shutteth his eyes from seeing evil ;\f + \fr 33.15 \ft righteously: Heb. in righteousnesses\f*\f + \fr 33.15 \ft uprightly: Heb. uprightnesses\f*\f + \fr 33.15 \ft oppressions: or, deceits\f*\f + \fr 33.15 \ft blood: Heb. bloods\f*

He shall dwell on high : his place of defence \add shall be\add* the munitions of rocks : bread shall be given him; his waters \add shall be\add* sure.\f + \fr 33.16 \ft high: Heb. heights, or, high places\f*
Thine eyes shall see the king in his beauty : they shall behold the land that is very far off.\f + \fr 33.17 \ft that…: Heb. of far distances\f*
Thine heart shall meditate terror. Where \add is\add* the scribe ? where \add is\add* the receiver ? where \add is\add* he that counted the towers ?\f + \fr 33.18 \ft receiver: Heb. weigher?\f*

Thou shalt not see a fierce people , a people of a deeper speech than thou canst perceive ; of a stammering tongue , \add that thou canst\add* not understand.\f + \fr 33.19 \ft stammering: or, ridiculous\f*

Look upon Zion , the city of our solemnities : thine eyes shall see Jerusalem a quiet habitation , a tabernacle \add that\add* shall not be taken down ; not one of the stakes thereof shall ever be removed , neither shall any of the cords thereof be broken.

But there the glorious \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add will be\add* unto us a place of broad rivers \add and\add* streams ; wherein shall go no galley with oars , neither shall gallant ship pass thereby.\f + \fr 33.21 \ft of…: Heb. broad of spaces, or, hands\f*

For the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* our judge , the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* our lawgiver , the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* our king ; he will save us.  +  r 33.22  t lawgiver: Heb. statutemaker *

Thy tacklings are loosed ; they could not well strengthen their mast , they could not spread the sail : then is the prey of a great spoil divided ; the lame take the prey.\f + \fr 33.23 \ft Thy…: or, They have forsaken thy tacklings\f*
And the inhabitant shall not say , I am sick : the people that dwell therein \add shall be\add* forgiven \add their\add* iniquity.
